Not a hardcore action film fan
But DHURANDHAR is not just another action film.<br/><br/>I actually felt it to be something raw which takes you through a thrilling ride where you want to know more about every single character and the film does exactly the same. Rather than giving you adrenaline rush in every frame by some unnecessary action ,the film gradually opens and slowly takes over you.<br/><br/>A good storytelling, compelling screenplay, power packed performances, absolute banger bgm&#39;s and believable action sequences.<br/><br/>In short &quot;dhamaka&quot;
A slightly gory for the faint hearted.

Reality of Pakistan.<br/><br/>Point,Rating,Review Summary
1. Performances,9/10,&quot;Stellar Ensemble Cast. Ranveer Singh delivers a restrained, powerful performance as the undercover agent Hamza. Akshaye Khanna, as the gangster Rehman Dakait, is often hailed as a scene-stealer, matching the lead with his chilling presence.&quot;
2. Direction &amp; Vision,8/10,&quot;Aditya Dhar&#39;s Ambitious Scale. The film is lauded for its ambitious, large-scale direction and a clear vision that weaves a gritty spy thriller with a Godfather-esque underworld saga.&quot;
3. World Building,9/10,&quot;Immersive and Gritty. The detailed recreation of Karachi&#39;s Lyari gangwar and the complex nexus of crime, politics, and the ISI is considered a major strength, making the world feel authentic and dangerous.&quot;
4. Screenplay &amp; Plot,7/10,&quot;Compelling, but Stretched. The narrative is gripping and complex, inspired by real events like the Kandahar hijacking and 26/11. However, many critics felt the writing gets stretched in the first half, spending too much time on setup.&quot;
5. Runtime &amp; Pacing,5/10,&quot;Excessively Long. With a runtime of approximately 3 hours and 34 minutes, it&#39;s one of the longest Indian films. The pacing is uneven, which is a major drawback, though the film rarely feels tedious for those invested in the story.&quot;
6. Music &amp; BGM,8/10,&quot;Scintillating Score. The background score and music, which cleverly blend old classics with modern soundscapes, are a triumph that effectively elevates the film&#39;s intense mood and relentless pulse.&quot;
7. Action &amp; Violence,7/10,&quot;Raw and Unflinching. The action sequences are brutal and grounded, contributing to the film&#39;s realism. The violence is unapologetic, adding to the intense tone, though some scenes were noted for poor VFX.&quot;
8. Technical Aspects,8/10,&quot;High Production Value. The cinematography is spectacular, and the production design is realistic and fabulous, lending a top-notch craft quality to the film. Editing is decent but flagged as not top-notch in places.&quot;
9. Emotional Core,7/10,&quot;Patriotism with Subtlety. The film manages to convey the emotional toll and stress of the spy&#39;s life effectively. It touches on patriotism and national security without relying solely on jingoism, focusing on character-driven stakes.&quot;
10. Climax &amp; Sequel Setup,9/10,&quot;Intense Cliffhanger. The film ends on an explosive and masterful twist that completely re-contextualizes the lead character and sets the stage perfectly for the confirmed Part 2, leaving the audience highly anticipating the sequel.&quot;

